  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2018;Support for Older People affected by COVID-19&apos;</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Objective 1: 24,300 older people, caregivers and community members better understand and are able to take action to prevent transmission of COVID-19</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Objective 2: Primary health care facilities and service providers responding to COVID-19 are better able to support older people throughout the pandemic.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Objective 3: Increased awareness by policymakers and other stakeholders of the greater risks faced by older people in the COVID-19 pandemic and how best to respond.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">the project aims to ensure older people and their communities in Ethiopia, Lebanon and Pakistan are protected from COVID-19 and the wider impacts on their health and that global response plans and policies are age-inclusive.</narrative>
  </description>
